.ds n) explain_getresuid
.cp 0  \" Compatibility mode off.
.TH explain_getresuid 3
.SH NAME
explain_getresuid \- explain \f[I]getresuid\fP(2) errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_getresuid(3)" "explain \f[I]getresuid\fP(2) errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/getresuid.h>
.sp 0.3
.ad l
const char *explain_getresuid(uid_t *ruid, uid_t *euid, uid_t *suid);
.br
const char *explain_errno_getresuid(int errnum, uid_t *ruid, uid_t *euid,
uid_t *suid);
.br
void explain_message_getresuid(char *message, int message_size, uid_t
*ruid, uid_t *euid, uid_t *suid);
.br
void explain_message_errno_getresuid(char *message, int message_size, int
errnum, uid_t *ruid, uid_t *euid, uid_t *suid);
.ad b
.SH DESCRIPTION
These functions may be used to obtain explanations for errors returned by
the \f[I]getresuid\fP(2) system call.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SS explain_getresuid
.ad l
const char *explain_getresuid(uid_t *ruid, uid_t *euid, uid_t *suid);
.ad b
.PP
The \f[B]explain_getresuid\fP function is used to obtain an explanation of
an error returned by the \f[I]getresuid\fP(2) system call. The least the
message will contain is the value of \f[CW]strerror(errno)\fP, but usually
it will do much better, and indicate the underlying cause in more detail.
.PP
The \f[I]errno\fP global variable will be used to obtain the error value to
be decoded.
.TP 8n
\f[I]ruid\fP
The original ruid, exactly as passed to the \f[I]getresuid\fP(2) system
call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]euid\fP
The original euid, exactly as passed to the \f[I]getresuid\fP(2) system
call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]suid\fP
The original suid, exactly as passed to the \f[I]getresuid\fP(2) system
call.
.TP 8n
Returns:
The message explaining the error. This message buffer is shared by all
libexplain functions which do not supply a buffer in their argument list.
This will be overwritten by the next call to any libexplain function which
shares this buffer, including other threads.
.PP
\f[B]Note:\fP This function is \f[B]not\fP thread safe, because it shares a
return buffer across all threads, and many other functions in this library.
.PP
\f[B]Example:\fP This function is intended to be used in a fashion similar
to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.fi
.ad l
if (getresuid(ruid, euid, suid) < 0)
.ad b
.nf
{
.fi
.ad l
.in +4n
fprintf(stderr, "%s\en", explain_getresuid(ruid, euid, suid));
.in -4n
.nf
    exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
}
.fi
.ft R
.ad b
.RE
.PP
The above code example is available pre\-packaged as the
\f[I]explain_getresuid_or_die\fP(3) function.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
.SS explain_errno_getresuid
